in Chicago till my classes begin.

63
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,993
(Sighs)

64
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:48,475
Look, I got some interviews
together for you.

65
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:52,434
Qualified bookkeepers to replace me.
Resumes are on my desk.

66
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:55,950
15 grand a year tuition... I don't know
how you're gonna pull that off.

67
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:58,469
With a part-time job, Joel.

68
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:00,670
I promised after Mom and Dad died,

69
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,870
I'd do whatever
to keep this place running.

70
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:07,118
But I can't work in a garage all my life.
You know I've trained to be a dancer.

71
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:08,912
Yeah, I know.

72
00:05:10,280 --> 00:05:11,679
All right.

73
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,431
I'm outta here.

74
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,719
Boss, if she don't work here no more,

75
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:39,070
you think I could date her?

76
