Hello! Hello, hello, stop! Stop!

106
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:24,114
We received 2,000 tapes.

107
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:27,710
You're one of the 300 people
here today, congratulations.

108
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:30,479
But now I need more.

109
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:32,079
I... I don't understand.

110
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:35,272
We're looking for dancers
who can express real emotion,

111
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,755
not fragments of it.

112
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:41,350
Something softer, more sensual,
more feminine.

113
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:43,357
More honest.

114
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:47,232
Thank you, Miss Kirk.

115
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:52,599
Who's next?

116
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:57,159
OK, let's get right to it.

117
00:09:58,360 --> 00:09:59,873
Right here.

118
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:19,999
Thanks.

119
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,712
252, huh?

120
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:26,559
I remember that cattle call.
It's a tough school.

121
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:28,639
You auditioned?

122
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:32,275
Oh, I don't know
if I'd exactly call it an audition.

123
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:34,630
I lasted all of a minute and 12 seconds.

124
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:37,668
Should I even ask?

125
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:43,032
It's harder than you thought
it was gonna be, huh?

126
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:46,835
At least my brother back home
will be thrilled to know I didn't get in.

127
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:50,316
Yeah, all my brothers and sisters live
in the same town where we grew up.

128
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:55,275
They thought I was crazy moving here.
My dad didn't speak to me for weeks.

129
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:57,391
Did it get better?

130
00:10:57,520 --> 00:11:00,159
Yeah, now he calls me all the time.

131
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:03,671
That school only lets in one percent.

132
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:06,792
That's like 20 out of the thousands
who apply,

133
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:09,593
so don't be so hard on yourself.

134
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:27,788
(Phone rings)

135
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,194
Hello?

136
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:35,878
So how'd it go?

137
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,479
OK.

138
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:41,318
- You didn't get in?
- 'I didn't say that.'

139
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:46,318
- So you did get in?
- They don't tell you right away.

140
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:49,955
- Well, what does it look like?
- Looks good.

141
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:54,795
- 'That sounds believable.'
- Look, Joel, I'm tired. OK, I...

142
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:57,388
- 'Call me as soon as you know.'
- Yeah.

143
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:59,431
(Car alarm wails)

144
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:01,630
I gotta go.

145
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:04,399
Wait! Stop!

146
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:07,273
Stop! Wait, stop!

147
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:09,999
Stop!

148
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:28,071
(Thunderclap)

149
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:40,755
(Door opens)

150
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:42,836
Hey, are you all right?

151
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:46,873
Let's get you out of this rain.
Call the tow company from my place.

152
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,718
Come on.

153
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:56,957
I really appreciate this.

154
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:59,640
No problem. Trust me, I've been there.

155
00:12:59,760 --> 00:13:03,514
When I first got here, I got knocked
down so many times I lost count.

156
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:06,473
And the looks,
like you're just some hick from...

157
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,511
Indiana? Mm-hmm.

158
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:12,111
Oh, what am I gonna do?

159
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:15,038
My brother thinks I'm going
to dance school. What do I tell him?

160
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:19,153
"I didn't get in.
And, oh, yeah, they towed my car, too."

161
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:22,750
I can't go home.
There's nothing for me there.

162
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:25,872
- So don't go.
- What, you mean stay in Chicago?

163
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:30,039
If you don't mind sleeping on the couch,
crash here while you figure it out.

164
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:32,833
Wait, you don't snore, do you?

165
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:35,110
Not the last time I checked.

166
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,599
Lauryn Kirk.

167
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:23,472
- Klirk?
- No. Kirk.

168
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:26,709
- No, I don't have you down here.
- I think it's...

169
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:29,434
You gonna have to go wait over there.

170
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:06,234
(# Dance music blaring)

171
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:23,637
Excuse me. Can I ask who you're with?

172
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:27,309
Oh, I was... er...
I was invited... here by a friend.

173
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:30,557
- Through the service door?
- Right... er...

174
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:33,148
- Can I see your ID?
- Yeah, of course...

175
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:38,712
- I'm really sorry about this.
- That's OK.

176
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:42,150
Lauryn Kirk from Glenwood, Indiana.

177
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:44,589
"Corn and cars", that's our motto.

178
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,119
I like corn.

179
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:48,674
Actually if you just give me
your phone number,

180
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:52,156
we can settle this,
and it's kind of a house rule...

181
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:54,032
- Hey, you made it.
- Hey.

182
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:56,355
- Is this guy giving you a hard time?
- No!

183
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:59,111
But I thought he was the manager.

184
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:01,800
The manager?
No, Russ is the music director.

185
00:16:01,920 --> 00:16:03,512
Guilty.

186
00:16:04,760 --> 00:16:07,877
- Nice try.
- Well, it almost worked.

187
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:11,197
Sort that out later.
I wanna introduce you to Brenda.

188
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:12,958
Bye, Lauryn Kirk!

189
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:22,479
Brenda, this is Lauryn and vice versa.

190
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:26,070
You've been looking for her,
for the bookkeeping job.

191
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:28,634
Thanks, but I'm not adopting
any more strays.

192
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:31,877
I need you upstairs getting ready.

193
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:36,070
Wait, wait.

194
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:38,714
I know you don't want a stranger
looking into your books,

195
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:41,877
but I know QuickBooks,
I can do payroll in my sleep,

196
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:45,197
and your quarterly 1087
is due in seven days.

197
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:49,074
If you pay your crew in cash, you'll need
a perfect Schedule E to avoid enquiries.

198
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:53,034
I've cranked those out like clockwork for
my family's business since I was 17.

199
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:56,914
But if you just need me to file stuff,
I can do that, too.

200
00:16:57,040 --> 00:17:00,032
- You done?
- Yeah.

201
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:03,277
Fine. Trial basis, $12 an hour,
and no benefits.

202
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:04,799
OK.

203
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:13,233
(Brenda) This is where the girls change.
This is your home away from home.

204
00:17:13,360 --> 00:17:16,352
You get paid every other week.

205
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:19,199
You'll start at 3:00
and stay till we close.

206
00:17:19,320 --> 00:17:23,359
If you can't find something, look harder.
It's all in here somewhere.

207
00:17:24,360 --> 00:17:26,191
You can start...

208
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:30,437
...by organising the January receipts.

209
00:17:30,560 --> 00:17:32,152
No problem.

210
00:17:32,280 --> 00:17:36,034
Oh, by the way, the other bookkeeper...
lasted about a week.

211
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:53,877
(Russ) Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to Ruby's,

212
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:56,309
the hottest spot in Chicago!

213
00:17:56,440 --> 00:17:59,079
(Clapping and cheering)

