236
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:12,720
(Dana and Lauryn laughing)

237
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:17,753
Hey, don't be late again.

238
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:19,279
Aye-aye.

239
00:21:21,080 --> 00:21:23,753
- This goes on every night?
- Every night we're open.

240
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:26,235
Brenda's got a real vision for the place.

241
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:30,035
It's rooted in burlesque, but our dance
goes way beyond the traditional stuff.

242
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:33,277
- Well, you were terrific up there.
- Thanks.

243
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:36,472
What's up, girls? Good job tonight.

244
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:40,195
- Brenda, hit me.
- Yes, wash this stuff down.

245
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:43,153
Hey, this is Lauryn.
She's the new bookkeeper.

246
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:47,118
Carmen's not interested
in any stories she's not the star of.

247
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:50,152
Oh, still bummed I'm not the star
of your world any more?

248
00:21:50,280 --> 00:21:53,670
- Baby, stars burn out.
- Maybe you couldn't stand the heat.

249
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:56,917
You guys wanna do some
after-hours damage at Junior's?

250
00:21:57,040 --> 00:21:59,634
- Yes. Cheers.
- (All) Cheers!

251
00:22:01,840 --> 00:22:04,798
- Right, first round's on Lauryn!
- What?

252
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:07,795
(Shouting and jeering)

253
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:15,595
(# LADY SOVEREIGN: "Hoodie")

254
00:22:39,480 --> 00:22:42,711
Can we have a Cosmo
and a gin and tonic, no ice?

255
00:22:42,840 --> 00:22:43,989
Hey, two.

256
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:08,359
Let's get this party started.

257
00:23:08,480 --> 00:23:11,870
(# LP featuring JOSE FUEGO:
"Pick It Up")

258
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:31,154
Aw, well, welcome to Chicago.
Congratulations on the new job.

259
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:35,676
Cool about earlier?
Cos I was just playing.

260
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:39,872
- So how long you worked at Ruby's?
- About a year.

261
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:43,996
- You like it?
- There's worse ways to make a living.

262
00:23:44,120 --> 00:23:46,315
I'll bet there are.

263
00:24:02,640 --> 00:24:05,791
- Why aren't you out there?
- Not my kind of dancing.

264
00:24:05,920 --> 00:24:10,311
Sitting back, hiding in your hoodie...
That's your kind of dancing?

265
00:24:13,280 --> 00:24:15,555
So... er... you and Carmen?

266
00:24:15,680 --> 00:24:17,511
No. No.

267
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:20,279
That was like a 24-hour flu.

268
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:24,552
You get it, you get really sick,
and then you get over it.

269
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:36,872
So arrogant. "Are you just hide
out there in your hoodie?"

270
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:41,949
Russ likes giving people a hard time,
especially if he thinks they're cute.

271
00:24:42,080 --> 00:24:44,071
Please.

272
00:24:44,200 --> 00:24:47,078
Russ was right.
You should've been on the floor with us.

273
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:49,953
What, dancing like Carmen? Shakin' it?

274
00:24:54,960 --> 00:24:56,791
(Dana) Work it. Ha!

275
00:24:57,800 --> 00:24:59,552
I love it.

276
00:24:59,680 --> 00:25:04,037
Seriously, you're missing another side
you could bring to your dancing.

277
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:06,276
I'm not dancing right now, remember?

278
00:25:22,880 --> 00:25:25,394
Hey, you're looking good.

279
00:25:27,600 --> 00:25:30,319
Why do my feet hate me?

280
00:25:30,440 --> 00:25:34,035
I don't know. Maybe it's cos
you're going from the twist into a step.

281
00:25:34,160 --> 00:25:36,071
Like you're missing something.

282
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:39,112
- Right. I'll just eighty-six the combo.
- No, it's...

283
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:44,519
No, I think the combination's fine.
It's just I think you're missing a piece.

284
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:47,029
Like, if it was my thing

285
00:25:47,160 --> 00:25:51,836
and I wanted to do that
I would just go... here to there.

286
00:25:51,960 --> 00:25:54,713
Hmm...
Could you show me that again?

287
00:25:54,840 --> 00:25:56,353
Sure, it's simple.

288
00:25:57,320 --> 00:25:59,151
- Here.
- Here...

289
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:01,316
Then here.

290
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:03,271
Then there.

291
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:05,789
- There... I like that.
- Yeah?

292
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:08,309
Watch your back, D.
Girl's got moves.

293
00:26:08,440 --> 00:26:12,672
- Maybe you should watch yours.
- Her moves ain't that good.

294
00:26:15,320 --> 00:26:18,278
Maybe you should give it a try,
get up on stage one night.

295
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:19,799
Are you kidding?

296
00:26:19,920 --> 00:26:23,390
I would fall on my ass in those heels.
Seriously, people would get hurt.

297
00:26:23,520 --> 00:26:26,990
- Shut up, you've got steps.
- No, it's not my thing.

298
00:26:27,120 --> 00:26:29,873
Oh, OK, and those clothes are?

299
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:32,514
Seriously, Lauryn,
they're killing your sexy.

300
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:36,349
- My sexy?
- Yeah, every dancer's got a sexy.

301
00:26:36,480 --> 00:26:39,950
You just got to find yours.

302
00:26:40,080 --> 00:26:43,197
(# ELISABETH WITHERS:
"Get Your Shoes On")

303
00:26:43,320 --> 00:26:45,515
# That's how we do it on the weekend

304
00:26:45,640 --> 00:26:48,916
# Turn up the radio
and let the speakers blow

305
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:53,477
# Get your shoes on,
feel the party go get started... #

306
00:27:10,320 --> 00:27:12,231
Without further ado,
ladies and gentlemen,

307
00:27:12,360 --> 00:27:15,955
put your hands together for Dana!

308
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:19,356
(# ROISIN MURPHY: "Ruby Blue")

309
00:27:22,840 --> 00:27:24,558
Go, Dana!

310
00:28:28,760 --> 00:28:30,671
(Applause and cheering)

311
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:44,355
Hey, Lauryn, meet Marcus.

312
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:46,630
Oh, hi. Dana's told me all about you.

313
00:28:46,760 --> 00:28:50,230
You should've seen your girlfriend
on stage tonight. She nailed it.

314
00:28:50,360 --> 00:28:51,713
Really?

315
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:54,149
We're gonna catch a bite to eat.
Wanna to join us?

316
00:28:54,280 --> 00:28:57,113
Oh, no, you two go.
I've got to finish up here...

317
00:28:57,240 --> 00:28:58,832
Yeah, you sure?

318
00:28:58,960 --> 00:29:02,475
- Yeah.
- OK, all right. Well, catch you later.

319
00:29:02,600 --> 00:29:05,194
- Like tomorrow.
- Bye.

320
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:07,390
- Have a good night.
- Bye.

321
00:29:08,960 --> 00:29:10,951
(Sighs heavily)

322
00:29:26,600 --> 00:29:29,034
OK, I'm out of here.

323
00:29:30,400 --> 00:29:31,799
Hello?

324
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:36,319
Anybody here?

325
00:31:18,360 --> 00:31:21,352
(Lauryn) I can't believe he said that.
(Dana) Me either.

326
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:23,277
(Phone rings)

327
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:30,915
You're still not taking
your brother's calls?

328
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:34,316
Just not up for it.
He still thinks I'm in school.

329
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:37,113
You can't hide here
and avoid him forever.

330
00:31:37,240 --> 00:31:39,993
- You've got to tell him sometime.
- I know.

331
00:31:40,120 --> 00:31:42,156
OK.

332
00:32:06,720 --> 00:32:10,633
- Come on, Cinderella.
- I gotta work, you guys go.

333
00:32:10,760 --> 00:32:12,512
(Growls)

334
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:14,471
Bye, see you.

335
00:32:15,960 --> 00:32:20,112
(Knocks) Hi. Nice moves.

336
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:23,357
- What are you?
- I'm not gonna tell anybody.

337
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:25,675
But just a hint...

338
00:32:25,800 --> 00:32:28,109
If you want to keep a secret,

339
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:30,993
don't rehearse where you work,

340
00:32:31,120 --> 00:32:34,669
unless you know you're the only one
with a set of keys.

341
00:32:37,240 --> 00:32:39,959
Thanks, I'll try to remember that.

342
00:32:41,360 --> 00:32:42,759
You know, er...

343
00:32:43,880 --> 00:32:46,872
Think I could pry you away?
Maybe grab a drink?

344
00:32:48,320 --> 00:32:50,675
Not real thirsty.

345
00:32:52,760 --> 00:32:54,159
Cool.

346
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:58,237
Cool. Er... next time.

347
00:33:00,280 --> 00:33:01,759
I could eat.

348
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:07,151
Well, I got the perfect place.

349
00:33:12,440 --> 00:33:15,671
Growing up, my mom used
to tell me stories about Chicago,

350
00:33:15,800 --> 00:33:19,156
the lights, energy, the people.

351
00:33:19,280 --> 00:33:22,033
She dreamed of coming here
and being a dancer.

352
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:25,869
- That's where you got the moves from.
- Yep. She studied to be one.

353
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:30,357
Chose to be a mom instead.
So she passed the dream down to me.

354
00:33:30,480 --> 00:33:33,552
- Is she still in Glenwood?
- No, no. She passed away.

355
00:33:35,640 --> 00:33:37,995
I'm sorry.

356
00:33:38,120 --> 00:33:41,635
She got pretty sick when I was about 10,

357
00:33:41,760 --> 00:33:45,070
and it took a lot out of us,
especially my dad.

358
00:33:45,200 --> 00:33:49,352
After Mom, he just...
spent all his time in the garage.

359
00:33:50,120 --> 00:33:52,793
He said it kept his mind off missing her.

360
00:33:54,760 --> 00:33:57,228
And then one night, three years ago,

361
00:33:57,360 --> 00:34:00,272
I was coming back to the garage
after a recital.

362
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:04,552
Joel was in Indy picking up equipment
and he'd asked me to stay with Dad.

363
00:34:04,680 --> 00:34:08,673
But some dancer friends
wanted to go out to dinner.

364
00:34:08,800 --> 00:34:11,360
Later when I did get to the garage...

365
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:15,354
...I found him on the floor.

366
00:34:15,480 --> 00:34:17,914
He'd had a heart attack.

367
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:22,639
I always wonder if I'd just got there
10 minutes earlier...

368
00:34:22,760 --> 00:34:25,558
You can't do that to yourself.

369
00:34:26,760 --> 00:34:31,914
After that, I put school on hold
to stay and help Joel out with the shop.

370
00:34:32,040 --> 00:34:35,555
Since losing Dad,
it's just been the two of us.

371
00:34:37,120 --> 00:34:39,554
That had to be hard.

372
00:34:39,680 --> 00:34:41,750
You know, all of it.

373
00:34:41,880 --> 00:34:43,279
Yeah.

374
00:34:45,080 --> 00:34:46,593
(Sighs)

375
00:34:46,720 --> 00:34:48,676
So what's in there?

376
00:34:48,800 --> 00:34:52,270
This? This is the best
sweet and sour shrimp in Chicago.

377
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:53,879
- Really?
- Want some?

378
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:55,433
Sure.

379
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:02,910
Yeah, that's Lincoln Park,

380
00:35:03,040 --> 00:35:06,828
where all the kids hang out
with the students and what not.

381
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:09,428
Then you got downtown,
where the bankers are.

382
00:35:09,560 --> 00:35:11,915
That's pretty much Chicago.

383
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:14,879
Well...

384
00:35:15,720 --> 00:35:18,996
Thank you for a wonderful dinner.

385
00:35:19,120 --> 00:35:20,519
Anytime.

386
00:35:24,960 --> 00:35:27,918
I don't remember seeing that
on the menu.

387
00:35:28,040 --> 00:35:31,237
Yeah, well, that's the Chef's Special.

388
00:35:34,240 --> 00:35:35,958
Good night.

389
00:35:36,080 --> 00:35:37,672
Good night.

390
00:35:53,720 --> 00:35:56,632
- Hey.
- Hi.

391
00:35:56,760 --> 00:35:58,830
- How's it going?
- Good.

392
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:03,194
So I had a good time last night.

393
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:04,719
Me, too.

394
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:08,435
You have got to be kidding me.
Carmen's running late.

395
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:10,949
Doesn't Dana go on first anyway?

396
00:36:11,080 --> 00:36:14,197
Do you see Dana?
No, because she called in sick.

397
00:36:14,320 --> 00:36:17,278
- And I have a line...
- I can spin till Carmen gets here.

398
00:36:17,400 --> 00:36:20,233
I have three birthday parties
and a room full of VIPs.

399
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:23,830
No offence, Russ,
but they didn't come to hear you spin.

400
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:26,918
- You could let Lauryn dance.
- What?

401
00:36:27,040 --> 00:36:29,838
Brenda, I've seen her dance,
OK, she's good.

402
00:36:29,960 --> 00:36:33,236
Why don't you just give her a shot?

403
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:38,229
Look, Lauryn, you're a sweet kid,
but you're obviously no dancer.

404
00:36:41,160 --> 00:36:42,752
Why did you tell her that?

405
00:36:42,880 --> 00:36:45,110
What, you're gonna hide out
back here?

406
00:36:45,240 --> 00:36:47,390
What you saw me doing
was fooling around.

407
00:36:47,520 --> 00:36:50,796
- I don't dance like Ruby's girls.
- So do your thing.

408
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:54,117
Trust me, when you get on stage,
nobody's gonna care.

409
00:36:54,240 --> 00:36:55,798
Well, I care.

410
00:36:57,480 --> 00:36:59,630
You moved to Chicago to be a dancer.

411
00:36:59,760 --> 00:37:02,638
I moved here to go to school.

412
00:37:03,880 --> 00:37:05,598
OK.

413
00:37:05,720 --> 00:37:07,312
I'm sorry.

414
00:37:09,560 --> 00:37:13,075
(Brenda) Look, price doesn't matter
as long as you get her here.

415
00:37:13,200 --> 00:37:14,758
Yes, a cab.

416
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:20,075
How long? All right.
Thanks, I'll give them a try.

417
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:28,315
Joe, it's Brenda,
I need a girl right away.

418
00:37:28,440 --> 00:37:30,032
Give me a shot.

419
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,718
I can do it.

420
00:37:38,560 --> 00:37:41,632
(# "Steamy")

421
00:37:46,800 --> 00:37:48,916
(Cheering and clapping)

422
00:37:57,840 --> 00:37:59,876
(Glass smashes)

423
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:03,356
(Booing and laughing)

424
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:13,389
(Woman) Get off the stage!

425
00:38:13,520 --> 00:38:15,715
What is this, amateur night?

426
00:38:22,240 --> 00:38:25,437
(Jeering and booing)

427
00:38:31,560 --> 00:38:34,552
(# LIL MAMA: "Shawty Get Loose")

428
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:45,958
(Cheering and whistling)

429
00:40:00,240 --> 00:40:02,800
We have a tradition.
After your first dance...

430
00:40:04,320 --> 00:40:06,914
...a toast on the house.
- Thank you.

431
00:40:07,040 --> 00:40:10,953
If I didn't know any better,
I'd say you rehearsed for tonight.

432
00:40:11,080 --> 00:40:12,798
Beginner's luck.

433
00:40:12,920 --> 00:40:15,195
"Beginner"...you got that right.

434
00:40:19,760 --> 00:40:21,273
Well...

435
00:40:21,400 --> 00:40:23,868
...that just proves
how good you were tonight.

436
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:26,434
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

437
00:40:26,560 --> 00:40:29,632
You wanna get out of here?

438
00:40:34,040 --> 00:40:36,429
(Russ) Really?
You grew up around a garage?

439
00:40:36,560 --> 00:40:38,710
(Lauryn) Yeah, I know
my way around a car.

440
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:42,515
- I'd like to see you as a grease monkey.
- Oh, yeah.

441
00:40:42,640 --> 00:40:46,235
That'd be Joel's dream come true,
keeping me in that shop.

442
00:40:46,360 --> 00:40:51,229
- Well, he's just a protective brother.
- A little too protective.

443
00:40:51,360 --> 00:40:56,275
He doesn't want me to get my hopes up,
so he means well, I guess.

444
00:40:57,720 --> 00:41:01,872
- This is really impressive.
- It's my entire life, right here.

445
00:41:03,440 --> 00:41:05,908
- That yours, too?
- Mm-hm.

446
00:41:06,040 --> 00:41:09,555
Yeah, I gotta admit something
that's been bothering me for a while.

447
00:41:09,680 --> 00:41:11,750
What's that?

448
00:41:11,880 --> 00:41:13,472
I lied.

449
00:41:15,040 --> 00:41:17,679
When I said I liked corn,
that was a blatant lie.

450
00:41:17,800 --> 00:41:20,234
I actually hate corn.

451
00:41:20,360 --> 00:41:24,478
Wow. I feel betrayed, like I don't
even know you any more...

452
00:41:26,560 --> 00:41:31,270
- Play me something you wrote.
- What, now? No. No, it's...

453
00:41:31,400 --> 00:41:33,356
Quit stalling, Music Man.

454
00:41:35,720 --> 00:41:37,517
OK.

455
00:41:37,640 --> 00:41:39,437
OK.

456
00:41:39,560 --> 00:41:43,792
This one I'll play you is...
It's not finished yet.

457
00:41:43,920 --> 00:41:48,232
And... er... you know, don't judge it.
OK, please?

458
00:41:48,360 --> 00:41:50,430
- OK.
- OK.

459
00:41:51,720 --> 00:41:53,950
(# Jazzy dance tune)

460
00:42:03,320 --> 00:42:04,958
This is you?

461
00:42:05,080 --> 00:42:07,071
Yeah, I just, I looped the vocals.

462
00:42:07,200 --> 00:42:10,397
- On the sax, that's you, too?
- Mm-hm.

463
00:42:13,080 --> 00:42:15,435
You should play more.

464
00:42:16,240 --> 00:42:17,832
You're good.

465
00:42:17,960 --> 00:42:19,359
Thanks.

466
00:42:21,720 --> 00:42:24,871
So that's pretty much it.

467
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:27,798
- It's not finished.
- Why not?

468
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:31,434
Cos I haven't got around to it.

469
00:42:35,680 --> 00:42:38,114
I think someone's eager
to change the subject.

470
00:42:38,240 --> 00:42:39,912
Yeah. Yeah.

471
00:42:40,040 --> 00:42:43,669
This your thing?
Going though all the girls at the club?

472
00:42:43,800 --> 00:42:46,360
- Mm-hm, all of them.
- That's what I thought.

473
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:49,438
First Carmen and then who else?

474
00:42:49,560 --> 00:42:52,393
You know,
somebody needs to shut you up.

475
00:42:52,520 --> 00:42:54,670
- Oh, really?
- Mm-hm.

476
00:43:03,200 --> 00:43:06,875
- What's wrong?
- I think I had too much to drink.

477
00:43:08,360 --> 00:43:12,194
Well, then, you... er... shouldn't drive.

478
00:43:14,960 --> 00:43:18,509
I'm sorry, I don't...
I don't think I'm ready for that yet.

479
00:43:20,080 --> 00:43:23,072
That's not what I was talking about.

480
00:43:42,760 --> 00:43:45,354
(# ALANA D: "Break It Down")

481
00:44:47,280 --> 00:44:49,874
(Phone rings)

482
00:44:57,200 --> 00:44:59,350
(Sighs heavily)

483
00:45:00,480 --> 00:45:03,119
Hey. Got your email.

484
00:45:03,240 --> 00:45:06,835
Yeah, I was gonna call you. I got a job.

485
00:45:08,400 --> 00:45:12,757
- At a garage?
- No, at a club, called Ruby's.

486
00:45:14,440 --> 00:45:18,035
OK, what's with the silence?

487
00:45:18,160 --> 00:45:21,755
Had to let Marty go.
It's no biggie, just a little downsizing.

488
00:45:21,880 --> 00:45:23,996
'So how's the school? '

489
00:45:24,120 --> 00:45:25,872
It's good.

490
00:45:26,000 --> 00:45:29,436
I sent you some stuff I found
in the attic I thought you might want.

491
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:31,915
- 'Some of Mom's things.'
- Thanks.

492
00:45:33,760 --> 00:45:37,799
I gotta go. I booked some studio time
and my class is starting, so I should...

493
00:45:37,920 --> 00:45:41,515
Yeah. Yeah, sorry. Take care.

494
00:45:58,720 --> 00:46:03,077
Lauryn, I have three regulars outside
asking when they'll see you dance again.

495
00:46:03,200 --> 00:46:05,760
I told them tonight. Can you be ready?

496
00:46:05,880 --> 00:46:07,438
Yeah.

497
00:46:12,280 --> 00:46:15,955
You haven't earned the right
to be on that stage.

498
00:46:16,080 --> 00:46:18,310
- Excuse me?
- Yeah, you're a dime a dozen.

499
00:46:18,440 --> 00:46:21,079
Just another girl from Bumbalow
trying to make it big.

500
00:46:21,200 --> 00:46:24,909
Guess what, this is the real world and
people come to see something special.

501
00:46:25,040 --> 00:46:27,600
Not that stuff you do.

502
00:46:27,720 --> 00:46:29,836
Bullshit, Carmen.
I've trained my whole life.

503
00:46:29,960 --> 00:46:31,313
Please.

504
00:46:31,440 --> 00:46:34,591
The tradition takes years to perfect.
You don't just roll in and own it.

505
00:46:34,720 --> 00:46:37,109
Lauryn, ten minutes and you're up.

506
00:46:38,440 --> 00:46:40,795
What's going on?

507
00:46:40,920 --> 00:46:44,879
Break a leg. Really. I mean it.

508
00:46:49,200 --> 00:46:52,112
Ladies and gentlemen,
let's give a warm Ruby's welcome

509
00:46:52,240 --> 00:46:55,516
to the newest addition
to the family... Lauryn!

510
00:46:55,640 --> 00:46:57,437
(Cheering)

511
00:46:57,560 --> 00:46:59,994
(# Unkle Jam: "Love Ya")

512
00:48:14,720 --> 00:48:17,029
Like you said, girl's got moves.

513
00:48:59,640 --> 00:49:03,474
So... er... this school
you auditioned for,

514
00:49:03,600 --> 00:49:06,672
did they say anything, you know,
like why you didn't get in?

515
00:49:06,800 --> 00:49:09,075
Sort of, I guess.

516
00:49:09,200 --> 00:49:11,270
Can I be honest with you?

517
00:49:11,400 --> 00:49:14,233
I think whoever made that decision
is nuts.

518
00:49:16,720 --> 00:49:20,679
OK, the director of the dance
department didn't like my routine.

519
00:49:20,800 --> 00:49:22,836
He said he thought it wasn't...

520
00:49:22,960 --> 00:49:25,952
sensual or feminine enough
or something like that.

521
00:49:26,080 --> 00:49:29,311
Let's wrestle him into Ruby's one night
and prove him wrong.

522
00:49:29,440 --> 00:49:32,477
I don't think he's looking
for Ruby's kind of dancers.

523
00:49:32,600 --> 00:49:35,068
This guy can't have final say
in your life.

524
00:49:35,200 --> 00:49:39,716
Well, no offence, but he is
a world-renowned choreographer,

525
00:49:39,840 --> 00:49:44,311
so I think he knows a little bit more
about dance than me and you.

526
00:49:44,440 --> 00:49:46,908
Well, I know what I see and...

527
00:49:47,040 --> 00:49:50,919
...I see that you could be as sexy
as Carmen if you wanted to be.

528
00:49:51,040 --> 00:49:53,270
Oh, really?

529
00:49:53,400 --> 00:49:55,231
You know what, Russ?

530
00:49:55,360 --> 00:49:58,909
My life's goal isn't
to be as sexy as Carmen.

531
00:49:59,040 --> 00:50:02,635
- Hey... I'm sorry, that came out wrong.
- Oh, you think?

532
00:50:02,760 --> 00:50:06,309
Yeah. This isn't about Carmen,
this is about you.

533
00:50:07,480 --> 00:50:10,392
You can mix it up better
than any of those girls at Ruby's,

534
00:50:10,520 --> 00:50:12,511
and trust me, I've seen 'em all.

535
00:50:12,640 --> 00:50:15,791
And you have the potential
to go so much further.

536
00:50:15,920 --> 00:50:17,911
That's all I was trying to say.

537
00:50:22,040 --> 00:50:23,951
What?

538
00:50:26,640 --> 00:50:28,392
Come on.

539
00:50:29,680 --> 00:50:32,877
Ow! You know, you're kind of cute
when you're mad.

540
00:50:33,000 --> 00:50:35,514
- I'm not talking to you.
- I'm just saying.

541
00:50:35,640 --> 00:50:36,868
Shut up!

542
00:51:26,640 --> 00:51:28,312
Mom...

543
00:51:36,880 --> 00:51:38,598
Hey.

544
00:51:38,720 --> 00:51:40,233
Hey.

545
00:51:40,360 --> 00:51:44,399
Your routine felt a little off tonight.
Something on your mind?

546
00:51:45,320 --> 00:51:48,949
Just... some stuff from back home,
I guess.

547
00:51:53,360 --> 00:51:57,831
My favourite teacher once told me...
dance is a window to the soul.

548
00:51:59,040 --> 00:52:01,235
It doesn't let you hide.

549
00:52:03,320 --> 00:52:05,880
But if you always fight what you feel,

550
00:52:06,000 --> 00:52:10,596
you'll never tap into what could
make you not just a good dancer

551
00:52:10,720 --> 00:52:12,233
but a great one.

552
00:52:14,920 --> 00:52:16,319
Yeah.

553
00:52:21,840 --> 00:52:23,717
Lock up when you leave, OK?

554
00:52:23,840 --> 00:52:25,239
OK.

555
00:54:05,280 --> 00:54:07,316
(# KEKE PALMER: "Bottoms Up")

556
00:54:07,440 --> 00:54:10,432
# Get off the wall,
don't matter what they think

557
00:54:10,560 --> 00:54:13,279
# From your fingertips
to your toes

558
00:54:13,400 --> 00:54:15,868
# You know you're hot,
so let everybody know

559
00:54:16,000 --> 00:54:19,197
- # Gotta take it low
- # Bottoms up, bottoms up...

560
00:54:27,200 --> 00:54:30,670
# Yeah, keep it movin', man,
make it poppin', man

561
00:54:30,800 --> 00:54:33,360
# I'm on the move,
gotta catch me when you can

562
00:54:33,480 --> 00:54:35,516
# Might see my face
on the movie screen

563
00:54:35,640 --> 00:54:38,154
# Hypnotise you frame by frame,
scene by scene

564
00:54:38,280 --> 00:54:40,555
# Get your head up, do your thang

565
00:54:40,680 --> 00:54:44,150
# Get off the wall,
don't matter what they think... #

566
00:55:18,160 --> 00:55:19,195
(Knocking)

567
00:55:19,320 --> 00:55:20,753
Coming.

568
00:55:30,920 --> 00:55:32,751
Is something wrong?

569
00:55:32,880 --> 00:55:34,711
No, not at all.

570
00:55:34,840 --> 00:55:37,229
You just look amazing. Come on in.

571
00:55:45,360 --> 00:55:47,351
You are a closet romantic.

572
00:55:49,000 --> 00:55:51,753
Well, I've been called worse.

573
00:55:55,280 --> 00:55:56,599
Shall we?

574
00:56:01,800 --> 00:56:03,438
Wait. Let me.

575
00:56:05,880 --> 00:56:08,235
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

576
00:56:11,360 --> 00:56:14,989
- May I offer you some wine?
- Yes, please.

577
00:56:17,800 --> 00:56:19,233
Thank you.

578
00:56:19,360 --> 00:56:20,759
(Sizzling)

579
00:56:20,880 --> 00:56:25,635
Oh, no. I gotta check the oven.
I'll be right back.

580
00:56:34,760 --> 00:56:37,035
How about a take-out?

581
00:56:38,240 --> 00:56:39,832
I don't know, it's like...

582
00:56:39,960 --> 00:56:42,952
...as long as the shop is alive,
a little piece of my parents is, too.

583
00:56:43,080 --> 00:56:46,356
So, it would kill me
if Joel ever closed it.

584
00:56:46,480 --> 00:56:50,553
- You two sound close.
- We've had our moments.

585
00:56:52,000 --> 00:56:54,309
So I wanted to thank you
for the other night.

586
00:56:54,440 --> 00:56:55,839
For what?

587
00:56:56,520 --> 00:56:58,238
You were right.

588
00:56:58,360 --> 00:57:01,511
I can't let somebody I've met once
decide what I want.

589
00:57:01,640 --> 00:57:06,395
So I did some research... and...

590
00:57:06,520 --> 00:57:10,957
...the School of Music and Dance usually
accepts 20 applicants in a school year.

591
00:57:12,200 --> 00:57:14,350
But this year only 18 qualified.

592
00:57:14,480 --> 00:57:17,472
So they're holding
a second round of auditions

593
00:57:17,600 --> 00:57:20,797
for the next semester
to find their remaining two dancers.

594
00:57:20,920 --> 00:57:22,672
You're gonna re-audition?

595
00:57:22,800 --> 00:57:26,554
I think so. In three weeks.

596
00:57:26,680 --> 00:57:29,478
...the problem was the record company
got in my business,

597
00:57:29,600 --> 00:57:31,875
trying to tell me how to do it,
you know.

598
00:57:32,000 --> 00:57:34,195
I thought I knew better, so...

599
00:57:35,840 --> 00:57:38,195
...so I walked away.

600
00:57:38,320 --> 00:57:41,915
- Just like that?
- Just like that.

601
00:57:42,040 --> 00:57:44,508
I backed out of the deal and...

602
00:57:45,240 --> 00:57:48,835
...fell in with the wrong crowd,
and... er...

603
00:57:48,960 --> 00:57:51,349
...and... er... you know?

604
00:57:51,480 --> 00:57:54,756
Eventually, I ended up at Ruby's,

605
00:57:54,880 --> 00:57:57,155
and I straightened myself out.

606
00:57:58,640 --> 00:58:00,710
See, here's the thing.

607
00:58:03,320 --> 00:58:07,916
See, everybody who walks away
from a dream has a reason.

608
00:58:10,280 --> 00:58:12,271
I think it's brave...

609
00:58:13,520 --> 00:58:16,193
...to take another shot.

610
00:58:19,680 --> 00:58:24,435
Sometimes I just feel like
I'm doing it all wrong.

611
00:58:24,560 --> 00:58:26,551
Well, you're not.

612
00:58:58,400 --> 00:59:00,436
# Listen to me...

613
00:59:00,560 --> 00:59:03,074
(# JAMELIA: "Beware Of The Dog")

614
00:59:25,800 --> 00:59:28,109
# You know how much you want him

615
00:59:28,240 --> 00:59:31,755
# You're trying to be cool about it,
you're trying to be big about it

616
00:59:31,880 --> 00:59:35,236
# You're constantly just denying

617
00:59:35,360 --> 00:59:39,876
# You're like a moth to a flame,
can hardly wait but listen

618
00:59:40,000 --> 00:59:42,878
# Cause I know what I'm saying... #

619
01:01:02,560 --> 01:01:05,199
(Cheers and applause)

620
01:01:20,520 --> 01:01:22,431
Joel, stop!

621
01:01:22,560 --> 01:01:23,959
Wait!

622
01:01:24,560 --> 01:01:27,552
- Could you put some clothes on?
- What are you doing here?

623
01:01:27,680 --> 01:01:29,955
I came to congratulate you
on getting into the school,

624
01:01:30,080 --> 01:01:32,389
only they've never heard
of a Lauryn Kirk.

625
01:01:32,520 --> 01:01:34,351
You call this chasing your dreams?

626
01:01:34,480 --> 01:01:36,914
Is this all the hard work
you've been doing?

627
01:01:38,080 --> 01:01:42,119
I didn't get in.
I didn't know how to tell you.

628
01:01:42,240 --> 01:01:45,789
But if you'd stuck around,
you'd see how difficult the routines are.

629
01:01:45,920 --> 01:01:48,718
- I saw enough.
- Why don't you listen for a change?

630
01:01:48,840 --> 01:01:51,638
I'm on the verge of losing the shop,
and I drove six hours for this.

631
01:01:51,760 --> 01:01:54,877
- What do you mean?
- I have to sell or the bank'll foreclose.

632
01:01:55,000 --> 01:01:56,797
- I can't make the payments.
- What?

633
01:01:56,920 --> 01:01:59,354
- Equipment, leases, everything.
- Why didn't you tell me?

634
01:01:59,480 --> 01:02:01,391
Why would you care?

635
01:02:01,520 --> 01:02:05,149
You're a big city girl now,
you're a dancer.

636
01:02:05,280 --> 01:02:07,669
Why have you always had
a problem with me dancing?

637
01:02:07,800 --> 01:02:10,394
You think the world revolves around you,
you always have!

638
01:02:10,520 --> 01:02:14,798
How dare you? I put my life on hold
for three years, Joel!

639
01:02:14,920 --> 01:02:19,550
And you put Dad on hold that night!
You should've been there, Lauryn!

640
01:02:27,520 --> 01:02:29,511
Hey, you OK?

641
01:02:37,320 --> 01:02:39,914
Maybe he was upset
because you were so bad.

642
01:02:40,040 --> 01:02:42,952
Ease off, Carmen. She was killing it.

643
01:02:43,080 --> 01:02:46,550
He drives hours to get here, then
has her embarrass the family name.

644
01:02:46,680 --> 01:02:49,831
- Hey, hey, stop, stop.
- (Lauryn) I'm sick of your shit.

645
01:02:49,960 --> 01:02:52,315
Enough!

646
01:02:52,440 --> 01:02:54,749
You happy, Carmen?

647
01:02:56,000 --> 01:02:57,399
God, girl.

648
01:03:03,520 --> 01:03:08,036
Lauryn! Lauryn, wait!
She's just trying to get in your head.

649
01:03:08,160 --> 01:03:10,833
She can get in line cos there's
enough going on in there already.

650
01:03:10,960 --> 01:03:12,951
Hey, come on.

651
01:03:13,080 --> 01:03:16,868
I know that this was a lot,
but he knows now.

652
01:03:17,000 --> 01:03:20,436
- You don't have to lie any more.
- What if he's right?

653
01:03:20,560 --> 01:03:23,358
All my life my family gave up
so much for me.

654
01:03:24,480 --> 01:03:26,277
What if I'm selfish?

655
01:03:26,400 --> 01:03:30,109
What are you going to do,
you just going to quit dancing?

656
01:03:30,240 --> 01:03:34,597
- Gonna quit living your life?
- Joel's the only family I have.

657
01:03:34,720 --> 01:03:36,711
I shouldn't be here
chasing some stupid dream.

658
01:03:36,840 --> 01:03:39,559
I should be home helping him.

659
01:03:41,000 --> 01:03:45,437
- I'm sorry, I have to go.
- Who do you think you're fooling?

660
01:03:45,560 --> 01:03:49,473
I know you're going home
because you're scared of that audition.

661
01:03:49,600 --> 01:03:50,874
What?

662
01:03:51,000 --> 01:03:54,629
If this was about your brother,
you'd have told him before tonight.

663
01:03:54,760 --> 01:03:56,079
What are you talking about?

664
01:03:56,200 --> 01:03:59,670
I know that you're running
because you're scared and that's it.

665
01:03:59,800 --> 01:04:03,634
I'm sorry if it shocks you that I'd help
my family out in a time of crisis,

666
01:04:03,760 --> 01:04:06,672
but that's how we do things
where I come from.

667
01:04:06,800 --> 01:04:11,191
Lauryn, come on.
Lauryn, you're making a big mistake.

668
01:04:16,480 --> 01:04:17,879
Lauryn!

669
01:04:41,080 --> 01:04:43,719
What are you doing here?

670
01:04:45,160 --> 01:04:47,720
I found two new wholesalers
we can use.

671
01:04:47,840 --> 01:04:52,868
- That should catch us up half-way.
- Wait, just slow down for a second.

672
01:04:53,000 --> 01:04:56,356
- Are you back here to work?
- I'm not gonna let you sell.

673
01:04:56,480 --> 01:04:59,153
We can catch up.

674
01:04:59,280 --> 01:05:02,716
Look, I...
said some things I didn't mean.

675
01:05:03,760 --> 01:05:05,398
I know.

676
01:05:05,520 --> 01:05:07,636
I'm sorry. OK?

677
01:05:09,440 --> 01:05:13,752
Can I just get back to this? I was almost
done with last month's reviews.

678
01:05:13,880 --> 01:05:15,438
Yeah.

679
01:05:15,560 --> 01:05:18,996
Look, are you sure about this, Lauryn?
Being back?

680
01:05:20,920 --> 01:05:23,388
It was Dad's shop.

681
01:05:23,520 --> 01:05:25,715
You know what it meant to him.

682
01:05:28,240 --> 01:05:29,639
Hey...

683
01:05:31,080 --> 01:05:33,150
...you remember that time

684
01:05:33,280 --> 01:05:36,078
that you got the bicycle
on your eighth birthday?

685
01:05:36,200 --> 01:05:40,830
Yeah, I drove it in the shop, crashed
into the Buick and chipped my tooth.

686
01:05:40,960 --> 01:05:42,791
Yeah!

687
01:05:47,160 --> 01:05:49,958
I can dance another time, Joel.

688
01:05:51,880 --> 01:05:53,916
I'm here now.

689
01:06:17,200 --> 01:06:18,952
(Phone rings)

690
01:06:23,640 --> 01:06:26,074
(Dialling tone)

691
01:06:27,880 --> 01:06:29,836
(Ringing)

692
01:06:36,040 --> 01:06:38,395
(Message service beeps)

693
01:06:38,520 --> 01:06:43,594
Hey, it's me.
Er... I was just calling to say hi.

694
01:06:43,720 --> 01:06:49,556
'And... er... I'm not burning
the chicken any more, so... '

695
01:06:51,280 --> 01:06:53,077
I hope you come back soon.

696
01:06:54,160 --> 01:06:55,593
'Bye.'

697
01:07:10,760 --> 01:07:13,149
(Dialling tone)

698
01:07:13,280 --> 01:07:15,191
(Phone rings)

699
01:07:20,480 --> 01:07:21,674
Hey, stranger.

700
01:07:21,800 --> 01:07:25,713
I hear the last school audition
is this weekend.

701
01:07:25,840 --> 01:07:27,239
I know.

702
01:07:27,360 --> 01:07:30,033
You're going to be there, right?

703
01:07:30,160 --> 01:07:34,073
You know, I'm just... I'm really...
buried in paperwork here and...

704
01:07:34,200 --> 01:07:37,988
(Dana) 'Come on, Lauryn.
Have you talked to Russ? '

705
01:07:39,400 --> 01:07:41,755
No. He called, but...

706
01:07:41,880 --> 01:07:44,075
'You should, you know.'

707
01:07:47,440 --> 01:07:49,351
Look, I'll talk to you later, OK?

708
01:07:49,480 --> 01:07:51,391
Yeah.

709
01:07:52,480 --> 01:07:53,879
Bye.

710
01:08:06,880 --> 01:08:08,916
(# Music plays)

711
01:08:09,040 --> 01:08:13,318
Oh, hey, I love this song.
Come on. Come on.

712
01:08:14,480 --> 01:08:15,993
I need an alternator permit.

713
01:08:16,120 --> 01:08:18,634
(# SALT 'N' PEPA: "Push It")

714
01:08:18,760 --> 01:08:21,354
For old time's sake.

715
01:08:22,160 --> 01:08:24,037
Wednesday?

716
01:08:24,160 --> 01:08:28,711
#... we know how to become
number one in a hot party show

717
01:08:28,840 --> 01:08:30,558
- # Now push it
- # Ah, push it

718
01:08:32,120 --> 01:08:35,271
- # Push it good
- # Ah, push it

719
01:08:35,400 --> 01:08:38,073
- # Push it real good
- # Ah, push it... #

720
01:09:15,840 --> 01:09:19,674
- Oh, hey, I thought you left already.
- Just finishing up.

721
01:09:19,800 --> 01:09:21,950
Yeah, it's never done, is it?

722
01:09:32,840 --> 01:09:34,831
After Mum and Dad,

723
01:09:34,960 --> 01:09:36,837
you never quit...

724
01:09:37,600 --> 01:09:39,591
...never threw in the towel.

725
01:09:42,160 --> 01:09:43,991
I guess.

726
01:09:44,120 --> 01:09:47,999
You're the most unselfish person I know.
And you know what?

727
01:09:48,120 --> 01:09:51,192
You have always been
one hell of a dancer.

728
01:09:53,880 --> 01:09:58,032
Don't know how it happened.
Certainly wasn't cos I encouraged you.

729
01:09:59,080 --> 01:10:01,753
Speaking of which, you're fired.

730
01:10:02,480 --> 01:10:05,517
What? Joel, without me
you'll lose Dad's shop.

731
01:10:05,640 --> 01:10:08,234
It's not Dad's shop any more, it's mine.

732
01:10:08,360 --> 01:10:11,477
And I have to take care of it, not you.

733
01:10:11,600 --> 01:10:15,036
Lauryn, I'm not going to let you
sell out your dreams to live mine.

734
01:10:15,160 --> 01:10:17,674
So you need to get in your car,

735
01:10:17,800 --> 01:10:22,032
drive back to Chicago
and kick that audition's ass.

736
01:10:22,160 --> 01:10:23,957
All right?

737
01:10:41,720 --> 01:10:43,631
Get out of here.

738
01:11:00,800 --> 01:11:03,360
(Russ) Lauryn!

739
01:11:03,480 --> 01:11:05,755
- What are you doing here?
- Where else would I be?

740
01:11:05,880 --> 01:11:08,553
Here, I made you a track.

741
01:11:09,960 --> 01:11:14,397
What are you waiting for?
Go do your thing.

742
01:11:29,160 --> 01:11:31,549
(# Classical piano music)

743
01:11:32,960 --> 01:11:34,951
(Judge) Thank you.

744
01:11:36,120 --> 01:11:40,159
- Excuse me, this is a closed session.
- Yes, I'm here to audition.

745
01:11:40,280 --> 01:11:42,669
- (Judge) Miss?
- Kirk. Lauryn Kirk.

746
01:11:42,800 --> 01:11:46,952
Right. We held a set of auditions
this morning for those re-applying.

747
01:11:47,080 --> 01:11:50,038
We're only seeing first-time applicants
this afternoon.

748
01:11:50,160 --> 01:11:52,310
But I just drove 300 miles.

749
01:11:53,080 --> 01:11:56,516
And my staff will do their best
to reschedule you for next year.

750
01:11:56,640 --> 01:11:58,915
No, thank you. I'm here now.

751
01:11:59,040 --> 01:12:03,989
Well... I trust you've brought something
more interesting than last time.

752
01:12:04,120 --> 01:12:06,190
Is that correct?

753
01:12:07,440 --> 01:12:09,556
I'll let you decide.

754
01:12:20,960 --> 01:12:24,430
(# LADY GAGA: "Just Dance")

755
01:14:21,400 --> 01:14:22,913
(Russ) Woo!

756
01:14:23,040 --> 01:14:25,110
That's how you do it!

757
01:14:27,000 --> 01:14:28,991
Thank you, Miss Kirk.

758
01:14:29,120 --> 01:14:32,829
I'm afraid you're right,
some things should not be rescheduled.

759
01:14:33,520 --> 01:14:35,158
See you next semester.

760
01:14:35,280 --> 01:14:38,272
- Thank you.
- (Russ) My girl! Right here!

761
01:14:41,720 --> 01:14:43,711
Congratulations.

762
01:14:59,520 --> 01:15:01,272
(Lauryn) Hi.

763
01:15:02,560 --> 01:15:05,711
She's not in the best mood.

764
01:15:07,760 --> 01:15:11,070
Only employees are allowed in
before we're open.

765
01:15:11,200 --> 01:15:12,918
I... er...

766
01:15:13,040 --> 01:15:16,999
- I just came by to get my cheque.
- Your cheque?

767
01:15:17,120 --> 01:15:20,317
After the jam you left us in
when you took off like that,

768
01:15:20,440 --> 01:15:22,317
you think I owe you a cheque?

769
01:15:22,440 --> 01:15:24,271
I'm really sorry.

770
01:15:24,400 --> 01:15:27,597
OK, I promise it had nothing to do
with Ruby's. I love this place.

771
01:15:27,720 --> 01:15:30,029
(All) Surprise!

772
01:15:30,160 --> 01:15:32,720
(Clapping and cheering)

773
01:15:32,840 --> 01:15:34,990
- Got you.
- What?

774
01:15:35,120 --> 01:15:37,076
(Cheering)

775
01:15:38,400 --> 01:15:41,517
Hey, congratulations.

776
01:15:42,240 --> 01:15:45,471
Hey, Lauryn, look...
I'm sorry about all the BS, OK?

777
01:15:45,600 --> 01:15:49,149
I was just giving you a taste
of what I got when I started.

778
01:15:49,280 --> 01:15:52,795
I'm just glad you're getting out of here
so I can get my stage back.

779
01:15:53,960 --> 01:15:56,269
- Congratulations, sis.
- I'm glad you came.

780
01:15:56,400 --> 01:15:58,595
- I'm proud of you.
- Can I have a turn?

781
01:15:58,720 --> 01:16:00,119
- Hi.
- Hi.

782
01:16:01,240 --> 01:16:04,994
- You'll be sorely missed around here.
- I'm only a couple of blocks away.

783
01:16:05,120 --> 01:16:09,007
Good cos I don't need any
distractions when I'm making my album.

784
01:16:09,720 --> 01:16:12,395
- It's about time.
- I know. Cheers.

785
01:16:12,520 --> 01:16:16,593
What's everybody standing around for?
Is this a dance club or what?

786
01:16:16,720 --> 01:16:19,359
(# CLASSIC: "So They Say")

787
